# Commit message footer

When creating git commits in this repository, append this footer after the
commit body (blank line separating body from footer):

```
Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>

Signed-off-by: wyn <simon.parry@karoshibee.com>
```

Example full message:

```
[fpga] short subject line

One or two sentences explaining why.

Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>

Signed-off-by: wyn <simon.parry@karoshibee.com>
```

Pass multi-line messages via a HEREDOC (do **not** rely on `git commit -s`
alone — it only adds `Signed-off-by`). Trailer order is fixed:

1. blank line after body
2. `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>`
3. blank line
4. `Signed-off-by: wyn <simon.parry@karoshibee.com>`

Apply to every new commit unless the user explicitly requests a different format.
